# Task: Multi-Constraint Check (Density 13)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, n: int) -> bool

# Objective:
Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 13 independent constraints:
1. n is greater than 2
2. n is not equal to 104
3. n is a multiple of 1
4. n is greater than 8
5. n is not equal to 110
6. n is a multiple of 2
7. n is greater than 14
8. n is not equal to 116
9. n is a multiple of 4
10. n is greater than 20
11. n is not equal to 122
12. n is a multiple of 5
13. n is greater than 26

  (constraints

    (constraint "n != 110")
    (constraint "n % 2 == 0")
    (constraint "n > 14")
    (constraint "n != 116")
    (constraint "n % 4 == 0")
    (constraint "n > 20")
    (constraint "n != 122")
    (constraint "n % 5 == 0")
    (constraint "n > 26")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Check if the integer n satisfies all of the specified constraints.")
    (rule "All constraints must be true for the function to return True.")

)

        Args:

        Returns:
        bool: True if n meets all constraints, False otherwise.
        """
        return (
            n > 2 and

            n % 1 == 0 and
            n > 8 and

            n % 2 == 0 and
            n > 14 and
            n != 116 and
            n % 4 == 0 and
            n > 20 and
            n != 122 and
            n % 5 == 0 and
            n > 26
        )
